In this article, President Donald J. Trump issues a proclamation recognizing September 15 through October 15 as National Hispanic Heritage Month. He acknowledges the contributions of Hispanic Americans to American society and culture, highlighting their role in areas such as entrepreneurship, science, art, music, politics, academia, government, and sports. Trump emphasizes the importance of faith, family, and hard work in the Hispanic American community. He also mentions the growing number of Hispanic-owned small businesses in America and the significant presence of Hispanic Americans in the Armed Forces. Trump expresses a commitment to strengthening relationships with Latin American neighbors and promoting democracy and free trade in the region. He calls upon public officials, educators, librarians, and all Americans to celebrate National Hispanic Heritage Month with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs.